@node "ToolTypes" "Tool Types"
@toc "Instructions"
Various options can be changed by altering the Tool Types in the Icon
Information window:

 - TITLE=ON/OFF            Turns the title picture either on or off.

 - FISH=<name of fish>     Allows different fish to be loaded (see
                           FishEditor documentation).

 - SOUND=ON/OFF            Allows sounds to be turned on or off; sound off
                           reduces the atmosphere of the fish, the memory
                           it consumes and the time it takes to load.

 - STATUS=ON/OFF           If on, the Fishtank loads as normal.  If off,
                           the Fishtank loads, then switches to Workbench
                           and runs in the background (see @{"Keys" link "Keys" 0}).
@endnode

@node "Keys" "Keys"
@toc "Instructions"
The following keys affect the program:

 - Esc         Quits to Workbench.

 - F1          Switches to Workbench, opening a small window.  Closing this
               window switches back to the Fishtank.  While Workbench is
               visible,
               @{fg shine}FISHTANK IS PAUSED@{fg text}.

 - F2          The same as F1, except
               @{fg shine}FISHTANK IS NOT PAUSED@{fg text}.
@endnode

