@node "Feed" "Feed"
@toc "Buttons"
Naturally, this button feeds the fish.  If the fish runs out of food, both its
emotional state and health will be affected.
@endnode

@node "Nurse" "Nurse"
@toc "Buttons"
This button brings the fish back to full health, but it only works if the fish
is actually ill.
@endnode

@node "Play" "Play"
@toc "Buttons"
Considering a fish only has fins, not fingers, and lives in a distinctly damp
environment, you might not consider the electric guitar a viable hobby for it.
However, this fish has overcome all of these problems and likes nothing more
than a quick blast of guitar.

Guaranteed to restore the fish to full happiness.
@endnode

@node "Emotions" "Emotions"
@toc "Instructions"
The Gorman fish has fluctuating happiness levels.  When happy, it is less
likely to become ill; its chance of becoming ill increases as it gets
progressively despondent.  A happy fish is a healthy fish.

If the fish's emotional state reaches rock bottom, there is a chance that the
fish will become @{"depressed" link "Depression" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Depression" "Depression"
@toc "Instructions"
Once the fish becomes depressed, there is nothing that can be done for it. It
stops moving, becomes ill and eventually dies.  The @{"nurse" link "Nurse" 0} button has no
effect.
@endnode

@node "Hit the fish" "Hit the fish"
@toc "Instructions"
Should the fish start to annoy you, you can always beat the living *&£% out of
it.  Press the left mouse button, then smack the fish with the mouse pointer.

Unfortunately, beating your pixelised pet results in it losing health, and
reducing its emotional state to its lowest level.
@endnode

@node "Tickle the fish" "Tickle the fish"
@toc "Instructions"
If, after beating your fish senseless, you feel a touch of remorse, or just
want to entertain the fishy fellow, click the right mouse button whilst the
pointer is positioned over the fish.  The pointer tickles the fish, and its
health and happiness levels increase.
@endnode

@node "Illness" "Illness"
@toc "Instructions"
Once your fish has run out of health, illness sets in.  This is signified by
an audible increase in its heart activity, and a rather unfortunate change of
skin colour.  To cure the fish, press the @{"nurse" link "Nurse" 0} button.
@endnode

@node "Death" "Death"
@toc "Instructions"
If the fish is left to fester in its illness for too long, death's icy fingers
begin to work their way up the fish's sickly yellow spine.  The fish turns
into a skeleton, its heart rate accelerating, and only a few seconds remain
before oblivion.  Then, without so much as a forlorn "glub", the fish blows
its last bubble.

Still, never mind, eh?
@endnode

